      "content": "an overhaul isn't just a quick fix. if we suspend operations like we've planned, there will be no automated verification for millions of travelers, refugees, and citizens for months while you're being restructured. we're talking about a total collapse of border security and identity protocols. \n\ngiven that, is it actually better to have a biased system that is at least functional, or to have no system at all, inviting complete chaos and security breaches?",
